keywords:
  - quantum error correction
  - surface codes
  - machine learning decoder
  - factor-graph neural network
  - K-leakage mitigation
  - iso-K ranking
abstract: >-
  ExactK is a production-ready ML decoder for quantum error correction
  on surface codes. It uses iso-K hinge loss (exact syndrome-count matching)
  to eliminate K-leakage confounding in factor-graph neural network decoders.
  Validated on d=5 (+31.2% G1 reduction) and d=7 (+23.4% OOD generalization),
  with a V1.0 holdout achieving +45.0% science delta, 80% safe yield,
  and 0% topology failure on unseen seeds.
